text: The fast brown fox leaps over the lazy dog.
A thousand mile journey begins with one step.
Not all glittering things are gold.
To be, or not to be: that is the question.
Doubts of today limit our dreams of tomorrow.
Those who are too busy to look for success usually find it.
Don’t count the days; make the days count.
The best way to invent the future is by creating it.
Every shot you don’t take is a missed opportunity.
Failure isn’t the end of success; it’s a necessary step.
